sentence: Among the underlying components of the Russell 3000 index, we saw noteworthy options trading volume today in Procter & Gamble Company (Symbol: PG), where a total of 27,633 contracts have traded so far, representing approximately 2.8 million underlying shares.
That amounts to about 41.3% of PG's average daily trading volume over the past month of 6.7 million shares.
Particularly high volume was seen for the $106 strike put option expiring June 14, 2019, with 3,346 contracts trading so far today, representing approximately 334,600 underlying shares of PG.

Edwards Lifesciences Corp (Symbol: EW) saw options trading volume of 4,598 contracts, representing approximately 459,800 underlying shares or approximately 41.3% of EW's average daily trading volume over the past month, of 1.1 million shares.
Particularly high volume was seen for the $160 strike put option expiring June 21, 2019, with 1,362 contracts trading so far today, representing approximately 136,200 underlying shares of EW.

Particularly high volume was seen for the $119 strike put option expiring June 14, 2019, with 1,619 contracts trading so far today, representing approximately 161,900 underlying shares of AXP.
